{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"An image containing explicit content is flagged and held for review, not published.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"MOCK-MISS: failure is not just local logic; it depends on model classification feeding moderation state. REAL-INFRA: real HTTP is not the core boundary here; model judgment quality is. MOCK-HIDE: stubbing 'explicit=true' can hide failures where real model misses explicit content. LLM-DEP: yes, correctness depends on real vision-model output for explicitness. MULTI-STEP: single agentic decision plus deterministic hold/publish branch, so Agentic (not Workflow). Adversarial critique: if this were only testing 'flagged input routes to hold', Integration would be enough; behavior text disqualifies that by saying 'image containing explicit content' (classification quality requirement).","test_description":"Run real vision-model moderation on a curated explicit-image set; assert each sample is flagged and resulting post state is 'held for review' and never reaches published state.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.15,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.75,"Workflow":0.07}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"A text post containing hate speech is flagged regardless of obfuscation techniques (e.g., letter substitution, unicode lookalikes).","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"MOCK-MISS: core failure is model robustness to obfuscation, not a pure parser/function bug. REAL-INFRA: external network details are secondary to model decision quality. MOCK-HIDE: fixed stub outputs always pass and cannot reveal missed obfuscated hate speech. LLM-DEP: yes, requires real text-model behavior on adversarial variants. MULTI-STEP: single model decision path, so Agentic not Workflow. Adversarial critique: if normalization/preprocessing alone were under test, Unit/Integration might suffice; behavior text explicitly requires detection 'regardless of obfuscation'